  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "The [Authorizer interface](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/auth/authorizer/interfaces.go#L76) only returns an error today. This means that clients tend to treat any error as a \"No\" and return forbidden (e.g. our main [apiserver handler](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/apiserver/handlers.go#L484)).\n\nOur authorizers have become more complicated (and have upstream dependencies in the case of the webhook). If the authorizer cannot make a decision, the apiserver should return a retryable error (probably a 503 or 504) rather than a 403 that the client will most likely not retry.\n",
